          {
            "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/13357482/comment/17281535",
            "id": "17281535",
            "author": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=sunilg",
              "name": "sunilg",
              "key": "sunilg",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Sunil G",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "Asia/Kolkata"
            },
            "body": "Hi [~ananyo_rao]\r\nYes. In the preemption module, we get all apps from the scheduler. Hence some of the apps may be in a pending state which cant be scheduled (due to AM limit etc). So I think this is a quick fix. ",
